decreaseScore

public void decreaseScore(int factor)
Decreases a score. This is used with the bag of words method. The factor is generally the number of terms. This function decrease the score slightly more than it needs to, so that these results don't show up too high.

Parameters:
factor - - the integer factor by which to decrease a score

setMatch

public void setMatch(boolean bMatch)
Sets the match value to true or false. This is used in the bag-of-words method, because a particular word in the term may have a perfect match that is not the perfect match for the whole query term

Parameters:
bMatch - a boolean value for what match should be set to
